{"source_key":"sha256-bef6e223e150e48b322b8afa44a3f339","record_index":94,"record_hash":"sha256:6e12bd817c025df7abcd1ce2134c811c1e4793865f6e019a6c4f6671fe692bcb","timestamp":"2026-05-20T17:59:28.591Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"user","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"Found 3 real issues.\\n\\n**Fix Now**\\n\\n1. **GitMeta storage shape leaks into capture orchestration.**  \\n   [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:28](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:28), [crates/but-agentlog/src/capture.rs:29](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/capture.rs:29)  \\n   `write_transcript_batch()` now returns `TranscriptCapture { accepted_records }`, but `capture.rs` only needs `.len()`. That makes turn-storage internals part of the capture boundary. Keep `AcceptedRecord` private to `gitmeta.rs`; return `usize` again or expose `records_written()` only.\\n\\n2. **`source_key` is stored redundantly and can drift.**  \\n   [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:32](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:32), [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:48](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:48), [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:62](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:62), [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:141](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:141)  \\n   A turn has `source_key` in the summary, top-level detail, and every `AcceptedRecord`. Current capture is single-source, so the per-record copy is duplicate truth. Worse, `capture_turn_key()` hashes the top-level `source_key` plus record hashes, not each record’s `source_key` at [gitmeta.rs:279](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:279), so the stored per-record field is not protected by the key. Remove `source_key` from `AcceptedRecord` for now.\\n\\n3. **Turn metadata validation is skipped on idempotent captures.**  \\n   [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:101](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:101), [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:108](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:108), [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:115](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:115)  \\n   The code validates `record-hashes`, dedupes, and returns early if no new records survived. That means a corrupt `:turns` key can be ignored forever on repeat captures, then fail later when one new record appears. Validate `:turns` once the parsed batch has capturable records, before the dedupe early-return.\\n\\n**Document Only**\\n\\n4. **Capture + association is not atomic.**  \\n   [crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:154](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:154), [crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:159](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:159)  \\n   `record_transcript()` writes project metadata before `associate_session()` runs. If association fails, capture still happened. This predates Pass 1, so I’d document the partial-success behavior unless the command contract says capture+associate must be all-or-nothing.\\n\\nNo new duplicated path normalization jumped out: `cli.rs` resolves repo/workdir and makes transcript paths absolute-ish, `capture.rs` canonicalizes/read-checks the transcript, and `gitmeta.rs` stays on repo metadata. Tests not run; this was review-only as requested.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T17:59:28.591Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user"}}}